- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with first-order logic and its extension with successor-invariant formulas. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses graph classes of bounded expansion, which is a topic related to graph algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the model-checking problem for successor-invariant formulas. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph classes and their properties. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses planar graphs and minor-excluded graphs, which are topics related to computational geometry.
